  "local_port": 49804,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I'm on Jio network. I am able to watch Youtube videos cleanly without much buffering but downloading speed is pathetic",
  "response": "If you're experiencing good streaming quality on YouTube while your download speeds are low on the Jio network, there are several factors you can consider:\n\n1. **Network Congestion**: During peak hours, network congestion may lead to slower download speeds, even if streaming services are optimized for low bandwidth.\n\n2. **Device Performance**: Check if your device is functioning properly. Sometimes, background applications can affect download speeds.\n\n3. **Distance from Tower**: If you're far from the nearest cell tower or in an area with poor coverage, it might affect your download speeds.\n\n4. **APN Settings**: Ensure that your Access Point Name (APN) settings are correctly configured. Incorrect settings can impact your internet speeds.\n\n5. **Check for Data Limits**: If you have a limited data plan, check to see if you have reached your data cap, which might slow down your speeds.\n\n6. **Test on Different Apps**: Sometimes specific apps may have their own issues. Test downloading files from different sources, such as a web browser or other apps.\n\n7. **Network Mode**: Make sure your phone is set to the correct network mode (e.g., 4G/LTE) to ensure you are getting the best possible speeds.\n\n8. **VPN Usage**: If you're using a VPN, it might affect your download speed. Try disconnecting it to see if it improves.\n\n9. **Run Speed Test**: Use online speed test tools to determine your current download and upload speeds, helping you understand where the problem might lie.\n\n10. **Contact Customer Support**: If the problem persists, consider contacting Jio customer support to check for any known issues or to troubleshoot further.\n\nBy troubleshooting these aspects, you may identify the cause of your slow download speeds.",
